      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against in-vitro measurements across five flow-speed operating points. Agreement within 12% for all points; RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all conditions. Validation was performed exclusively on the nominal pump geometry. Manufacturing tolerance extremes (e.g., impeller tip clearance at upper and lower specification limits) were not included in the experimental validation matrix and represent a known limitation of the validation evidence base."
